ibmIROCconfigWrite.name: ibmIROCconfigWrite
ibmIROCconfigWrite.description: This object is a trigger to cause the current config image in memory to be written to disk or flash. A SET of this object to write(2) performs the same action as the T6 write command. A GET of this object with always return a value of noaction(1).

agentMemUse.name: agentMemUse
agentMemUse.description: This object indicates the current amount (in bytes) of dynamic memory allocated and in use by the SNMP agent. It is primarily in place to watch for any potential 'memory leaks', whereby, memory is allocated but never freed. This condition is indicated by an ever increasing value for this gauge.

authTrapSourceIPAddr.name: authTrapSourceIPAddr
authTrapSourceIPAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address of sender of the MIB request that fails authentication. An authentication failure trap is generated when the SNMP agent recives a MIB request does not have the proper community name.

platformType.name: platformType
platformType.description: The platform type containing this SNMP agent.

platformDRAMSize.name: platformDRAMSize
platformDRAMSize.description: The amount of dynamic RAM (Megabytes) installed on this platform. DRAM is used to contain the routing software and associated data areas.

platformFLASHSize.name: platformFLASHSize
platformFLASHSize.description: The amount of flash memory (Megabytes) installed on the 2210. Flash is used to hold configuration and software code loads, one pair of which can be loaded and made active on the platform. This object applies only to 2210, since other platforms' may or may not have FLASH, and if so, the size is not of interest. For these platforms, this object will take on a value of 0.

platformNVRAMSize.name: platformNVRAMSize
platformNVRAMSize.description: The amount of non-volatile memory (Kilobytes) installed on the 2210. NVRAM, sometimes referred to as SRAM, is used to hold the active configuration records. This object applies only to 2210, since other platforms' may or may not have NVRAM, and if so, the size is not of interest. For these platforms, this object will take on a value of 0.

platformFeatureSlot.name: platformFeatureSlot
platformFeatureSlot.description: The type of adapter installed in the feature slot of the 2210 platform. Note that not all adapter types listed above are currently supported, nor does this imply they will be supported in the future.

pppLCProtoState.name: pppLCProtoState
pppLCProtoState.description: The value identifies the present state of the PPP link. The closed(1) state indicates that the link is down and there is no attempt being made to open it and all connection requests from peers are rejected. In listen(2) state, the link is down and there is no attempt being made to open it, however, all the connection requests from peers are accepted. The state request-sent(3) indicates that an active attempt is being made to open the link. In this state, a Configure-request packet has been sent and no Configure-Ack has yet been received. In the state ack-received(4), a Configure-request packet has been sent and Configure-Ack packet has been received. The state ack-sent(5) indicates that a Congigure-request and Configure-Ack packets have been sent and Configure-Ack has not yet been received. The opened(6) state implies that a connection has been made and data may be sent. The state term-sent(7) indicates that an attempt is being made to close the connection and that a Terminate-request packet has been sent and a Terminate-Ack packet has not yet been received.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperTable.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperTable
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperTable.description: Information about multicast groups of which this DLSw is currently a member.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperEntry.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperEntry
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperEntry.description: Information about a single multicast group of which this DLSw is a member.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperIndex.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperIndex
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperIndex.description: The index to the conceptual row of the table. Values are assigned by the agent and are not reused, but continue to increase in value.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperRole.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperRole
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperRole.description: The role that this DLSw plays within the group. The first three roles are used by the IBM multicast DLSw group feature. The next three roles are used when interoperating with DLSw Version 2 compliant partners that may not have the IBM group feature.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperJoinTime.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperJoinTime
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperJoinTime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this DLSw node last became a member of this group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperConfigIndex.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperConfigIndex
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperConfigIndex.description: The value of dlswTConnConfigIndex of the dlswTConnConfigEntry that governs the configuration information used by this ibmdlswTConnGroupOperEntry. A management station can therefore normally examine both configured and operational information for this multicast group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInDataPkts.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInDataPkts
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInDataPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages of type DATAFRAME received for this group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutDataPkts.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutDataPkts
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutDataPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages of type DATAFRAME transmitted for this group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInDataOctets.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInDataOctets
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInDataOctets.description: The number of octets in Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages of type DATAFRAME received for this group. Each message is counted starting with the first octet following the SSP message header.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutDataOctets.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutDataOctets
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutDataOctets.description: The number of octets in Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages of type DATAFRAME transmitted for this group. Each message is counted starting with the first octet following the SSP message header.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInCntlPkts.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInCntlPkts
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperInCntlPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages received for this group which were not of type DATAFRAME.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutCntlPkts.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutCntlPkts
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperOutCntlPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages transmitted for this group which were not of type DATAFRAME.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperCURexSents.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperCURexSents
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperCURexSents.description: The number of CanUReach_ex messages sent for this group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperICRexRcvds.name: ibmdlswTConnGroupOperICRexRcvds
ibmdlswTConnGroupOperICRexRcvds.description: The number of ICanReach_ex messages received for this group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperCURexRcvds.description: The number of CanUReach_ex messages received for this group.

ibmdlswTConnGroupOperNQexRcvds.description: The number of NETBIOS_NQ_ex messages received for this group.

ibmdlswQllcLsTable.name: ibmdlswQllcLsTable
ibmdlswQllcLsTable.description: Table to provide an address mapping from configured QLLC addresses to DLSw MAC and SAP addresses, and other configured QLLC station information.

ibmdlswQllcLsEntry.name: ibmdlswQllcLsEntry
ibmdlswQllcLsEntry.description: The configured information for a single QLLC station.

ibmdlswQllcLsIfIndex.name: ibmdlswQllcLsIfIndex
ibmdlswQllcLsIfIndex.description: A unique identifier for the X.25 interface running QLLC through which this station is reached. This object is the same as the MIB-II ifIndex object.

ibmdlswQllcLsQdomain.name: ibmdlswQllcLsQdomain
ibmdlswQllcLsQdomain.description: X.25 circuit type identifier, permanent or switched

ibmdlswQllcLsQaddress.name: ibmdlswQllcLsQaddress
ibmdlswQllcLsQaddress.description: For PVCs, this is the logical channel number dedicated to this X.25 circuit. For SVCs, this is the DTE address of the remote QLLC device (i.e., the address that the DLSw node places a call to or receives a call from).

ibmdlswQllcLsChannel.name: ibmdlswQllcLsChannel
ibmdlswQllcLsChannel.description: Logical channel number for PVCs and connected SVCs. A value of zero indicates an SVC without a connected call.

ibmdlswQllcLsLocalMac.name: ibmdlswQllcLsLocalMac
ibmdlswQllcLsLocalMac.description: The MAC address that represents this QLLC station to other devices within the DLSw network.

ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteMac.name: ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteMac
ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteMac.description: The MAC address of a device in the DLSw network that this QLLC device can initiate a DLSw circuit to. If zero, the QLLC device cannot originate a DLSw circuit, but can only be the destination.

ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteSap.name: ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteSap
ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteSap.description: The SAP that accompanies ibmdlswQllcLsRemoteMac. If zero, the QLLC device cannot originate a DLSw circuit, but can only be the destination.

ibmdlswQllcLsPuType.name: ibmdlswQllcLsPuType
ibmdlswQllcLsPuType.description: SNA Physical Unit type of the QLLC device.

ibmdlswQllcLsBlkNum.name: ibmdlswQllcLsBlkNum
ibmdlswQllcLsBlkNum.description: SNA XID_0 block number for the QLLC device. A non-zero value implies that the DLSw node will generate an XID_0 on behalf of the device.

ibmdlswQllcLsIdNum.name: ibmdlswQllcLsIdNum
ibmdlswQllcLsIdNum.description: SNA XID_0 id number for the QLLC device. A non-zero value implies that the DLSw node will generate an XID_0 on behalf of the device.

frCLLMCauseIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value identifying the Frame Relay interface to which this CLLM cause information pertains.

frCLLMCauseCode.name: frCLLMCauseCode
frCLLMCauseCode.description: The cause code in the last CLLM message received on this interface.

frCLLMDlciList.name: frCLLMDlciList
frCLLMDlciList.description: The list of DLCIs contained in the last CLLM message received.

frTrapStateFECN.name: frTrapStateFECN
frTrapStateFECN.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the frrcvdFECN trap.

frTrapStateBECN.name: frTrapStateBECN
frTrapStateBECN.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the frrcvdBECN trap.

frTrapStateCLLM.name: frTrapStateCLLM
frTrapStateCLLM.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the frrcvdCLLM trap.

tcpiprouteTabSize.name: tcpiprouteTabSize
tcpiprouteTabSize.description: The configured number of entries that the routing table can maintain.

tcpiprouteTabUsed.name: tcpiprouteTabUsed
tcpiprouteTabUsed.description: The current number of routing table entries being used. The number includes both active and inactive entries.

tcpiprouteCacheSize.name: tcpiprouteCacheSize
tcpiprouteCacheSize.description: The configured number of entries that the routing cache can maintain.

tcpiprouteCacheUsed.name: tcpiprouteCacheUsed
tcpiprouteCacheUsed.description: The current number of routing cache entries being used.

tcpiprouteOverFlow.name: tcpiprouteOverFlow
tcpiprouteOverFlow.description: The number of routes that had to be discarded because the routing table was full.

tcpiprouteNoReach.name: tcpiprouteNoReach
tcpiprouteNoReach.description: The number of packets that could not be forwarded because of unknown destinations. This does not count the number of packets forwarded to the default gateway.

tcpiprouteBadSubnet.name: tcpiprouteBadSubnet
tcpiprouteBadSubnet.description: The number of packets and routes that have been received for illegal subnets (all ones or all zeroes).

tcpiprouteBadNet.name: tcpiprouteBadNet
tcpiprouteBadNet.description: The number of packets and routes that have been received for illegal IP destinations.

tcpiprouteUnhBcast.name: tcpiprouteUnhBcast
tcpiprouteUnhBcast.description: The number of non-local IP broadcasts received (which are not forwarded).

tcpiprouteUnhMcast.name: tcpiprouteUnhMcast
tcpiprouteUnhMcast.description: The number of IP multicasts received, but whose addresses were not recognized by the router (and are discarded).

tcpiprouteUnhDirBcast.name: tcpiprouteUnhDirBcast
tcpiprouteUnhDirBcast.description: The number of directed, non-local IP broadcasts received when forwarding of these packets is disabled.

tcpiprouteUnhLLbcast.name: tcpiprouteUnhLLbcast
tcpiprouteUnhLLbcast.description: The number of packets received having non-local IP addresses but were sent to a link-level broadcst address (and are discarded).

tcpiprouteDiscFilt.name: tcpiprouteDiscFilt
tcpiprouteDiscFilt.description: The number of packets received that have been addressed to filtered networks or subnets (and are discarded).

tcpiprouteMultRcvd.name: tcpiprouteMultRcvd
tcpiprouteMultRcvd.description: The number of IP multicasts that have been received and processed successfully.

tcpCurrConnections.name: tcpCurrConnections
tcpCurrConnections.description: The current number of TCP connections, which can be in any state. This object and tcpMaxConnections are defined mainly to monitor the number of TCP connections and their affect on memory usage in the router.

tcpMaxConnections.name: tcpMaxConnections
tcpMaxConnections.description: The maximum number of TCP connections allowed. This object and tcpCurrConnections are defined mainly to monitor the number of TCP connections and their affect on memory usage in the router.

serverCurrConnections.name: serverCurrConnections
serverCurrConnections.description: The current number of connections to a local server application (for example, TN3270E or Web Cache). This object and serverMaxConnections are defined mainly to monitor the number of server connections and their affect on memory usage in the router.

serverMaxConnections.name: serverMaxConnections
serverMaxConnections.description: The maximum number of connections allowed to a local server application (for example, TN3270E or Web Cache). This object and serverCurrConnections are defined mainly to monitor the number of server connections and their affect on memory usage in the router.

frrcvdFECN.name: frrcvdFECN
frrcvdFECN.description: This trap indicates that a frame was received from the network on this virtual circuit and it indicated forward congestion.

frrcvdBECN.name: frrcvdBECN
frrcvdBECN.description: This trap indicates that a frame was received from the network on this virtual circuit and it indicated backward congestion.

frrcvdCLLM.name: frrcvdCLLM
frrcvdCLLM.description: This trap indicates that a CLLM message was received from the network.

mosMemLow.name: mosMemLow
mosMemLow.description: This trap indicates that the free heap amount has dropped below a given percentage of the total heap memory available. The default percentage is 10%, however this threshhold can be modified by the user via a patch variable.

elsTrap.name: elsTrap
elsTrap.description: When the routing subsystem ELS component is configured to generate SNMP traps, the following trap is generated. It contains a single varBind containing a text string in one of the two following formats. If ELS timestamping is enabled: hr:min:sec subsys_name.event_num: message_text For example - 09:32:56 IP.008: no rte 9.7.1.8 -> 9.7.4.3 dsc If ELS timestamping is disabled: subsys_name.event_num: message_text For example - IP.008: no rte 9.7.1.8 -> 9.7.4.3 dsc NOTE: The following subsystems cannot have their events sent in SNMP traps (ARP, ICMP, UDP, SNMP and IP (excluding IP access control events)). This restriction is due to the fact that these subsystems are involved in sending an SNMP trap and allowing them could cause an infinite loop in the router software.
